Package entrants.utils.graph.interfaces

Interface IUndirectedGraph<N extends NodeInterface,E extends EdgeInterface>

  • Type Parameters:
    N - Nodes' type
    E - Edges' type
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DiscreteKnowledgeGraph, UndirectedGraph, WeightedUndirectedGraph
    public interface IUndirectedGraph<N extends NodeInterface,E extends EdgeInterface>
    Interface for Undirected graphs. No assumptions are made about nodes and edges, except that they need to extend NodeInterface and EdgeInterface respectively. UndirectedGraphs are also beans, which mean you need to do the following when implementing this interface :
    • Fire the NODE_ADDED_PROP property when a new node is added
    • Fire the EDGE_ADDED_PROP property when a new edge is inserted
    • Fire the NODE_REMOVED_PROP property when a valid node is deleted
    • Fire the EDGE_REMOVED_PROP property when a valid edge is deleted

      • addNode

        boolean addNode​(N node)
        Add a new node in the graph. If the node was already registered, this is a no-op. This method fires a NODE_ADDED_PROP when a new node is added to the graph.
        Parameters:
        node - the node you want to add to the graph
        Returns:
        true if the node has been added, false if it was already registered in the graph

      • addEdge

        boolean addEdge​(E edge)
        Add a new edge in the graph. If the edge was already registered, this is a no-op. If nodes in the edge where not registered, this method will create them (and thus fire a NODE_ADDED_PROP property) This method fires a EDGE_ADDED_PROP when a new edge is added to the graph.
        Parameters:
        edge - the edge you want to add to the graph
        Returns:
        true if the node has been added, false if it was already registered in the graph

      • removeNode

        boolean removeNode​(N node)
        Remove a node from the graph. If not such node matches, this is a no-op. If the node is linked with others by edges, this method will also delete relevant edges (and thus fire a EDGE_REMOVED_PROP before node's effective deletion and NODE_REMOVED_PROP fire).
        Parameters:
        node - the node to be deleted
        Returns:
        true is the node has been deleted, false if this was a no-op

      • removeEdge

        boolean removeEdge​(E edge)
        Remove an edge from the graph. If not such edge matches, this is a no-op. Fires a EDGE_REMOVED_PROP property.
        Parameters:
        edge - the edge to be deleted
        Returns:
        true is the edge has been deleted, false if this was a no-op

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clear the entire graph. Method fires GRAPH_CLEARED_PROP property containing in oldValue the graph before deletion ie a map N -> Collection.

      • circleNode

        java.util.Map<N,java.util.List<E>> circleNode​(N node,
                                              java.util.Collection<N> circlingNodes)
        Given a node n and a bunch of nodes M, find nodes in M circling node n. It means that if C is the subset of M, for all node in C, there is a path between n and the node AND none of the nodes in C are contained in the path.
        Parameters:
        node - the node you want to circle
        circlingNodes - candidates for circling
        Returns:
        a map, associating each node with the path to reach n.
